These constants are used to calculate the energy released in fusion reactions involving deuterium\, tritium\, helium-3\, and protons. The energy fractions are calculated assuming a non-relativistic center of mass $'frame.\r' $'\r' The following constants have been $'added:\r' - dt_neutron_energy_fraction: Energy fraction carried by neutron in deuterium-tritium $'reaction\r' - dd_neutron_energy_fraction: Energy fraction carried by neutron in deuterium-deuterium \(helium-3 producing\) $'reaction\r' - dd_proton_energy_fraction: Energy fraction carried by proton in deuterium-deuterium \(triton producing\) $'reaction\r' - dhelium_proton_energy_fraction: Energy fraction carried by proton in deuterium-helion \(helium-3\) $'reaction\r' $'\r' These constants will be used in further calculations related to fusion $'reactions.\r' $'\r' CITATION.cff CMakeLists.txt CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md CONTRIBUTING.md LICENSE.txt README.md
